                <head>71. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On February 19, 1962, Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1"
                        >McNamara</persName>, Admiral <persName corresp="#p_FAHD1">Felt</persName>,
                    Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_NFEJ1">Nolting</persName>, General <persName
                        corresp="#p_HGPD1">Harkins</persName>, Assistant Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>, and numerous other
                    officials met at <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> Headquarters in
                    Honolulu for the third Secretary of Defenseʼs Conference. A full record of the
                    meeting is in Washington National Records Center, RG 84, Saigon Embassy Files:
                    FRC 68 5159, SGN (62) 19 <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>-DEFSEC-<gloss
                        target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss>. For a summary record, see <ref
                        target="#d77">Document 77</ref>. Regarding the second Honolulu Conference,
                    January 15, see <ref target="#d22">Document 22</ref>.</p>
            </div>
